==English==
===Etymology===
From ancient Greek "''autokrates''" (αυτοκρατής) "one who governs alone" , from "''autos''" (αυτός) "single, self, same, alone" + "''kratos''" (κράτος) "power".

===Noun===
'''autocracy'''
# form of [[government]] in which unlimited power is held by a single [[individual]]
